        patients with systemic sclerosis who used cardiac transplantation for primary cardiac
        involvemen
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion criteria:

          -  Adult patients meet the criteria for classification of systemic sclerosis

          -  Adverse primitive heart that required a heart transplant

          -  Patients who have given their verbal agreement to use their data for research
             purposes.

        Exclusion criteria:

          -  Localized Scleroderma or sclerodermiform syndrome

          -  Heart disease secondary to pulmonary or renal impairment

          -  Refusal to participate in the study
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
